# Spotify Clone API - Authentication Tests
# You can use VS Code REST Client extension to run these tests

### Health Check
GET http://localhost:3000/health

### Register new user
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "testuser@example.com",
  "username": "testuser",
  "password": "Password123",
  "display_name": "Test User"
}

### Login with test user
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "testuser@example.com",
  "password": "Password123"
}

### Login with existing seed user
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@spotify.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### Get user profile (replace TOKEN with actual token from login)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/users/me
Authorization: Bearer TOKEN_HERE

### Update user profile (replace TOKEN with actual token)
PUT http://localhost:3000/api/users/me
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer TOKEN_HERE

{
  "display_name": "Updated Test User",
  "avatar_url": "https://example.com/avatar.jpg"
}

### Change password (replace TOKEN with actual token)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/change-password
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer TOKEN_HERE

{
  "current_password": "Password123",
  "new_password": "NewPassword123"
}

### Test invalid registration (missing fields)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "invalid-email",
  "username": "a"
}

### Test invalid login
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "nonexistent@example.com",
  "password": "wrongpassword"
} 